techmeme.title: Eve, which makes AI tools for law firms, raised a $47M Series A led by a16z, and says its revenue has grown by 5x over the past eight months (Allie Garfinkle/Fortune)
Brokerage firm IG Group acquires UK trading app Freetrade for £160M; Freetrade raised ~£30m via crowdfunding and was valued at £650m in 2021 during the pandemic (John Reynolds/Tech.eu)
UK's Ofcom imposes robust age checks on porn sites, which could include photo ID matching, facial age estimation technology, and credit card checks (Daniel Thomas/Financial Times)
Anduril plans to build a $1B factory in Columbus, Ohio called Arsenal-1 to eventually produce tens of thousands of autonomous systems and weapons each year (New York Times)
China plans to probe whether the US gives its chipmakers an unfair advantage through grants or undercuts Chinese products illegally, escalating the chip war (Bloomberg)
